Want to know a secret to getting your first pull-up?! 🤫

Well…you need to be able to HANG 😅 and YES you can come “hang” with us @pulluprevolution

So I know hanging seems pretty straight forward but it’s not. I honestly always did it because someone told me if I hang enough it would make me taller….but I’m still short 😂

So here are a few things YOU can do to get comfortable with “hanging out”

✅ Just Hang for as long as you can

Completely relaxed just chill, time yourself and see how long you can do it for. Typically, if you can hang for at LEAST 30seconds you are in a good spot

✅Try an Active Hang

This is a different type of hang that really activates those lats, which is the main reason why most people are struggling with their pull-up. Hold for 10seconds, relax and repeat! See if you can do this at least 3 times without dropping.

✅ Just Move Around the Bar

Yup literally just mess around on the bar. Move around, like a monkey. Play, enjoy it.

✅Mess around with flipping your hands
Try flipping your hands around on the bar

All the things I have written above are GREAT ways to get started with learning your pull-up! It will increase your confidence and build grip strength! And its not an overwhelming place to start!

Where are YOU at with your Pull-up Currently? How long can you HANG? 👇🏻👇🏻

The secret to reaching your goals…

I have been doing this since 2017 (actually 2016) and it WORKS.

And before you say ‘yeah right’ I want to explain WHY it actually works vs what you might think! 

✅Since using this process I have successfully
✅Competed on Ninja Warrior 4x 
✅Graced 3x Magazine Covers (one cover I legit put on my vision board in 2016, I photoshopped myself on it 
✅Opened a Gym 
✅Created a 6 figure Online Business 
✅Worked with UnderArmour (my dream brand)

I do something called Goal Setting and Vision Boarding. 

Some people think Vision Boarding you put your dreams on a poster and just expect them to happen…that’s not how it works…

By getting clear on what you want, it’s more likely to happen and you are less likely to get distracted. 

And when you see it infront of you each day you are more likely to take small actions to get towards you goals. 

What I have realized is that NOTHING is impossible, it just takes time & consistency! And sometimes it shows up differently OR when you least expect it! 

Wednesday I am doing a Goal Setting Workshop to walk you through my entire process that I’ve done each year (yes, it will be recorded)

⚡️Eight Phases of Getting your Pull-up
⠀
Getting your pull-up is NOT a linear Journey..it’s literally a rollercoaster ride. One day you feel strong the next day you feel like you took ten steps backward. ⠀
⠀
It’s so important to understand and identify what phase you are in so that you know the right areas to work. Knowing the phases also allows you to mentally see your path to success⠀
⠀
Because let’s be honest...getting a pull-up can feel impossible & frustrating. And the time it takes you to get your pull-up depends on how much time you are willing to dedicate to it, the central nervous system (mind & body connection) to make it happen & of course strength. ⠀
⠀
So check out the phases I have created below to help my clients clearly identify where they are at so that we can focus on the right areas to accelerate their pull-up progress . ⠀

➡️Phase 1: Can hang of the bar for a few seconds but that is it ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 2: Can hang the bar for 20-30seconds at least and get that initial shrug of the pull-up but is stuck getting anywhere past that point ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 3: Hanging is no problem at all, you can shrug and get a slight bend in those elbows ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 4: You can shrug and get about halfway in that pull-up but you might be using your shoulders to much and you start pulling with one side more that the other (unevenly) ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 5: You are able to get one full pull-up, it may not be easy and you might be using your shoulders a bit but you get that chin up there! ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 6: You first pull-up is seeming easier and now you are trying to connect 1-3 Pull-ups ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 7: Cranking out 1-3 Pull-ups with no problem but slows down after that ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 8- Cranking out 5 or more pull-ups with no problem ⠀
⠀
⠀
My question to you….what phase are YOU in?! 👇🏻⠀

Taking today to recap 2022. I think so many times we think of all the “negative things” or what we “didn’t have chance to do” during recaps. But I want to remind you to celebrate the things that DID happen FOR you ;). 

I started 2022 by finally taking the leap and moving to Austin Texas. Every time I came back here, it just felt like home. I would always be extending my stays, I always felt the amazing energy. So instead of “waiting” I took a chance.

Got an apartment in a single day…had to figure out how to get someone to take over my lease at my Colorado place and move my stuff to Austin. Within a few days, someone took over my lease, I flew back to Colorado, rented a big car and STUFFED it with the things I had and made the 14 hour drive STRAIGHT to my new empty apartment in Austin. 

My 2022 year was about Alignment & I def feel like I got that. 

I learned hard lessons that tested me, allowing me to dive deeper into WHO I want to be and what I need to let go of in my life in order for that to happen. 

Here’s 11 Lessons I learned in 2022 

👉🏻Set Boundaries and then STICK to them otherwise you will keep seeing the same problems in life 

👉🏻Ask for what you want, without fear of judgement 

👉🏻If your anxious you’re living in the future if you’re depressed your living in the past 

👉🏻Once you actually let go and LIVE your life instead of trying to control it…is when everything happens 

👉🏻Money WONT make you happy BUT it def makes things LESS Stressful 

👉🏻Hard conversations are necessary but they don’t need to be painful 

👉🏻The SIMPLE things are the most meaningful 

👉🏻There is not ONE right way to do something 

👉🏻Just because someone gives you advice doesn’t mean you need to take it 

👉🏻Coconuts are better from the tree

👉🏻Half Cafs are a game Changer 

Ready for 2023?! What did you learn!?

I really wanted to end my life…but I didn’t because of this advice. 

This is a vulnerable yet real story. And a lot of people don’t make it out on the other side. I was lucky to have a great mentor to help me along the way. 

We attach ourselves to an identity of being an athlete, maybe the a career, maybe it’s being a mom. But a reminder, you are so much more than JUST that. 

Even without any of those things…YOU MATTER ❤️.

My hope is by sharing my journey it will help others who might feel stuck like I did. 

I know IG shows a highlight reel of most of our lives, but we all have gone through or are going through something. This is the very “real”’journey about life. 

I tell you what though. I am grateful for everyone of these moments because I learned so much about myself & it molded me into the person I am today. 

When you overcome obstacles and adversity it builds character, it builds resilience. 

You can and will get through it all and be even stronger ! So hang in there ❤️

My morning routine looks like this “most of the time” 

If I can’t do it all in the AM I at least make a conscious effort to do it throughout the day. 

Routines are NOT supposed to stress you out, they are to help make you better. 

I remember getting so frustrated if I wasn’t perfect with it and then I realized…the point isn’t to be perfect. The point is to do something and to put my health first <3 

✅Meditation:
I do a quick 5-10min on directly in my bed I use an app called @headspace which guides you through it! 

✅Journaling:
I write about life, gratitude, affirmations and the ‘what if it all goes right’ framework 

✅Read:
I aim to just read 1 page, because your girl is a slow reader. This month I am readying the  best seller the psychology of money. If I read more great! But goal is just ONE page..not 10, not a chapter, just one.

B/c you just gotta !

How do I know how much protein I am eating? 

You might have been seeing a lot of information out there about how important it is to hit about 1g of protein per pound per day which is about 30-50 grams of protein per meal. I personally am 126 pounds so I should aim for 126g of protein. 

But what does 30-50g of protein even look like? I want to show you an example of a meal and break down the estimate protein about in it! I will go through each part of the meal and then estimate the TOTAL grams at the end! See if you can guess before I post it! 

Potatoes = ~3g Protein 
Greenbeans = ~1.8g Protein 
Carrots = ~1.8g Protein 
Brussel Sprouts = ~3g Protein 
3oz Chicken = ~35g Protein 

To the plate of ONE serving I have here would be…

Total = ~35 + ~0.45 + ~0.45 + ~0.75+ ~0.75 = ~37.4g

Why you should do Weighted Pull-ups 💁🏻‍♀️?! 

I love this moment because…how many times do we do something our coach tells us that we don’t want to do 🤣 but we know is good for us. 

I also have days where I just don’t wanna do it…but that’s why it’s good to have that extra push from someone ! 

I remember in college gymnastics, I used to do full routines on uneven bars with my sneakers on to add a little extra weight…and when I took them off to do my routine I FLEW through it. And when I do weighted pull-ups I think of that moment.

I train a TON of clients that want multiple pull-ups (I actually have a specific 6 week program made JUST for you so let me know if you want deets on that)

But here are some benefits! 

1. Increased Strength: By adding weight to your pull-ups, you’ll be increasing the resistance, which will help build more strength in your upper body muscles. This will in turn make it easier for you to perform more pull-ups without feeling as much fatigue.
2. Better Muscle Endurance: As you perform more weighted pull-ups, your muscles will adapt to the increased resistance, leading to improved endurance and the ability to perform more reps without feeling fatigued.
3. Increased Confidence: By successfully performing weighted pull-ups, you’ll be building confidence in your strength and abilities. This can help motivate you to keep pushing yourself and working towards your goals, leading to even more progress and the ability to perform even more pull-ups.

Lack Recovery JUST might be why you aren’t seeing results or getting stronger 🤷🏻‍♀️

Most people think the MORE I do the HEAVIER I lift every single day the stronger I will get and the more tone I will become….but that isn’t necessarily true…you need to recovery JUST as hard as you train..

What is recovery?
Recovery is rest days, SLEEP, Stress management <—things that matter but are often forgotten about or neglected 

Recovery is JUST as important as your workout and here’s why it’s even MORE important as we get older 

BTW I’m not saying you have to do ice bath everyday…

1- Slower Muscle Recovery: As you age, your body’s ability to repair and rebuild muscle tissue slows down. This means that after a workout, your muscles may take longer to recover, leaving you feeling sore and fatigued for a longer period of time.

2-Decreased Hormonal Levels: As you age, your body’s production of hormones like testosterone and human growth hormone decreases. These hormones play a crucial role in muscle growth and repair, so lower levels can make it more difficult for your body to recover from a workout.

3-Stress: your body’s ability to tolerate stress decreases with age, so you may need more time to rest and recuperate between workouts to avoid overtraining and burnout.

So if you’re running, working out 3x a Day, not giving your body proper time to recover and NOT seeing or feeling results I encourage you to play with recovering just as hard as you train. Take recovery days seriously!

6 Different Ways to Hang 
And why they are beneficial 

1️⃣Deadhang AKA Passive Hang 
 Which means completely relaxed on the bar! It can help to decompress the spine and stretch the muscles of the upper body. This can be especially beneficial for people who spend a lot of time sitting or hunched over a desk, as it can help to counteract the negative effects of poor posture. Additionally, passive hangs can improve grip strength and shoulder mobility.

2️⃣Active Hang 

An active hang is an exercise in which an individual hangs from an overhead bar or other stable structure while actively engaging the muscles in the upper body. Unlike a passive hang, the arms are not fully extended and the shoulders are not relaxed. Instead, the individual actively engages the muscles in the arms, shoulders, and core to hold the body in a hanging position. The goal of an active hang is to build strength and stability in the upper body, particularly in the shoulders, arms, and core. GREAT first step to conquering a pull-up 

3️⃣Hanging Move 

This allows you to become more confident on the bar, more aware of your body and strengthens your grip strength and core strength even more! 

4️⃣Hollow Hang 

This position engages the deep core muscles (Everyone loves that)  and can help to improve overall core strength and stability.

5️⃣Towel Hang 

This is the NEXT level hang to improve your grip and finger strength!

Five Pull-up Drills to help you get your pull-up at ANY Age! 

When you think of the pull-up, you want to strengthen it from the BOTTOM to the top!

So here are some drills you can do at ANY Age to start working towards your pull-up! We will go over more in the FREE Pull-up Workshop @homebodytrainer & I are hosting online ! Comment “Workshop” below for deets ! 

1️⃣ Hollow Hang 
The first step to getting a pull-up is being able to HANG on the bar! I always tell my clients to work towards being able to hang for a full 30seconds! This “hollow” hang is great because it also adds an additional core strengthening factor which is also important to conquer your pull-up!

2️⃣Active Hang 
After you feel more confident on you hangs! You can start trying “Active hangs” Instead of simply relaxing and letting gravity do the work, you squeeze your shoulder blades together, engage your core, and focus on maintaining tension in your body. This technique helps build strength in your upper back, shoulders, and arms, and improves your overall pull-up performance by enhancing muscle activation and stability.

3️⃣Shoulder Shrugs 
The hardest part of the pull-up IS the bottom! So when doing the shoulder shrug you are basically going from a relaxed hang to and active hang! Hold for 3 seconds at the top! And do these slow aim to be able to do 8-10 in a row! 

4️⃣Flexed Arm Hang 
we also need to learn how to keep tension on the bar and strengthen the TOP of the pull-up! So for the flexed arm hang you will START at the top of the bar! Use a chair or something to get you up there! Think BREAK the bar, pull your elbows IN & keep your shoulders relaxed! Hold for your max time and step back down on to your chair after! Goal is to try and get 20sec or so and start to feel more and more comfortable with this! 

5️⃣Eccentric Pull-ups 
What’s great about the eccentric is it elongates the muscles creating a tiny micro-tears that will help you build strength! BUT it’s hard 😅 Use a chair to help guide you on the way down and go slow especially at the bottom! The SLOWER the better!

Pull-ups hold the key to maintaining muscle health as we age, and Ginny is a living testament to that.

✅Also Pull-ups help increase grip strength which is a great indicator of overall health and longevity

Basically work on your pull-ups = live a longer and healthier life 

✅Plus, pull-ups aren’t just about physical strength.  This is a mental game about overcoming obstacles and pushing past your limits, both in the gym and in life.

Fit in your 30s vs Fit in your 60s doesn’t need to look different 💁🏻‍♀️

For so long, I always thought that as you get older you couldn’t learn something new because it was “too late”… if I couldn’t do it when I was younger how will I do it now…

But what a lie that is.. while yes, I do need to actually warm-up for my workouts and listen to my body a bit more than when I was younger…I can’t get away with doing random things anymore.. 

@sixtyandme is a perfect example that you can keep learning and do epic things with your body even as you get older in her 60s she is hanging for at least 1 minute a day, learning new moves and keeping her body moving! 

For so many the idea of getting a pull-up when you couldn’t do one in high school seems impossible when you get older.. but it’s not.. 

Here are 4 Moves you can do on and off the bar to get started on working towards your pull-up 

1️⃣Hollow Hang 
This is a double win movement it helps to increase your grip strength and core to help with your pull-up! 

2️⃣Towel Hollow Hold 
If you don’t have a pull-up bar work on a Hollow Hold with a Towel! Holding and pulling on the towel while keeping your core engaged mimics the hanging hollow hold but on the floor 

3️⃣Active Hang 
The hardest part of the pull-up is the BOTTOM! This Active hang helps retract those scapular and lets your body understand how to work that bottom part of the pull-up 

4️⃣Towel Superman Holds 
A great move to strengthen your grip strength and back without a bar 💁🏻‍♀️

What limiting beliefs are holding you back ?

Stop 🛑 thinking about getting your chin above the bar for your first pull-up…it’s holding ya back ! 
⠀
Getting your pull-up is NOT a linear Journey..it’s literally a rollercoaster ride. One day you feel strong the next day you feel like you took ten steps backward. ⠀
⠀
It’s so important to understand and identify what phase you are in so that you know the right areas to work. Knowing the phases also allows you to mentally see your path to success.
⠀
Because let’s be honest...getting a pull-up can feel impossible & frustrating. And the time it takes you to get your pull-up depends on how much time you are willing to dedicate to it, the central nervous system (mind & body connection) to make it happen & of course strength. ⠀
⠀
So check out the phases I have created below to help my clients clearly identify where they are at so that we can focus on the right areas to accelerate their pull-up progress . ⠀

➡️Phase 1: Can hang of the bar for a few seconds but that is it ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 2: Can hang the bar for 20-30seconds at least and get that initial shrug of the pull-up but is stuck getting anywhere past that point ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 3: Hanging is no problem at all, you can shrug and get a slight bend in those elbows ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 4: You can shrug and get about halfway in that pull-up but you might be using your shoulders to much and you start pulling with one side more that the other (unevenly) ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 5: You are able to get one full pull-up, it may not be easy and you might be using your shoulders a bit but you get that chin up there! ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 6: You first pull-up is seeming easier and now you are trying to connect 1-3 Pull-ups ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 7: Cranking out 1-3 Pull-ups with no problem but slows down after that ⠀
⠀
➡️Phase 8- Cranking out 5 or more pull-ups with no problem ⠀
⠀
⠀
My question to you….what phase are YOU in?! 👇🏻 if you want to learn how to finally get your pull-up with ease comment “workshop” down below ! To join use for our free online pull-up workshop Sunday ! ⠀

I ate cheesecake for breakfast...

Yup...you heard it. I am a fitness coach and yet..sometimes I each cheesecake for breakfast.🤷🏻‍♀️ and here’s why… 

 I personally used to deprive myself of all my favorite foods when I was training for fitness competitions… and I was miserable.

I was constantly craving pumpkin muffins, cookies, ginger-ale (I know... that’s a weird one) and bread

After I competed I would go NUTS. I legit ate everything I could find, and afterwords I felt like shit, and then I just couldn’t get back on track.😅 Maybe you’ve done this before during the holiday? 

So the next time I competed, I tried something DIFFERENT. I ate all the nutritious food but I also had a pumpkin muffin or cookie everyday.

And guess what.. my body looked exactly the same on show day, and afterwards I didn’t freak out and go nuts.

By enjoying the food I love and not stressing about it, I looked and felt better and I was able to stay consistent and not “fall off track”

I think there is a negative and stressful connotation with holiday food. But here’s the deal... if you stay consistent with your food and do simple, short workouts throughout the holidays, then you can HAVE the yummy food AND keep that energy up!
 
Things that DON’T Work:
❌ Not eating for days after you had some yummy food
❌ Doing a TON of cardio to try and burn it all off
❌ Feeling so guilty and stressed about what you ate that you just wait til Monday… which becomes next month... which becomes next year...
❌ Labeling the food as bad
 
Things that DO work:
✅ Being CONSISTENT with your food by giving your body the nutrients it needs
✅ Being on a CONSISTENT, structured workout program that are quick and easy! 
✅ Enjoying the f*** out of your favorite foods, because food is AWESOME
✅ Not labeling any food as bad

👉You gotta keep those shoulders healthy 🥳! And huge reason why all my @pulluprevolution are successful is because I emphasis mobility & stability in their training so they can get their pull-up and have a strong foundation to limit injuries 

It’s important to recognize that the rotator cuff has a lot of muscles and moves in various
directions, so you’ll want to warm it up in all directions before getting into a tough upper body workout! 

👉Meet the four rotator cuff muscles: 
➡️Supraspinatus: Keeps your arm stable
➡️Infraspinatus: Lets you rotate and extend your shoulders
➡️Teres minor: The smallest rotator cuff muscle
➡️Subscapularis: The largest and strongest muscle of the rotator cuff

So you wanna warm ‘em up right? Try these four exercises with a resistance band:
➡️External rotations (put a towel under your elbow—this helps to make sure you keep the right position and allows more blood flow to the rotator cuff!)
➡️Internal rotations 
➡️External rotation at 90 degrees 
➡️Straight arm pull-downs

I huge missing piece to all the random drills you are doing online to get your pull-up is drills OFF the pull-up bar.

Most drills you are seeing online are…

➡️NOT helping with the hardest part of the Pull-up (which is the bottom) 

The assisted pull-up bad flings you up at the bottom of the pull-up making it super hard to get off the band and do it unassisted! 

These three drills use a LIGHT assisted band and focus on the BOTTOM and over emphasis the bottom !

2️⃣ Shrug to 1/4 Pull-up: works the BOTTOM part 
3️⃣ Shrug to a full pull-up
